Paul Warren (born December 22, 1953) is an American rock and blues guitarist, known for being a member of a few rock bands as well as the former touring guitarist for English rock singer Rod Stewart for eleven years, he was also with American rock singer Richard Marx.
Warren was also a member of Ray Manzarek's Nite City from 1977 till their disbanding in 1978.
